{
  "stem": "26576.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they put me in that room, and I was there quite a few weeks because this was catchy, and I was scared that-- that I haven't seen-- my mother never came once, even.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She couldn't walk.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father came a couple of times and got me some chicken soup, and-- because he was working, so from work, he dropped in.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was quite a while until I recovered and went back [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then this was from the time that we came, which this was a very-- when I think about all those years in Russia, this was our worst time from every point of view.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From we were haggard.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were starving.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From bitterly cold, and a lot of-- there was sickness.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A lot of people died from-- from there, and a lot of people were killed also, the ones that tried to run away and that.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were a lot of people like us that the Russians were uncomfortable with.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, they were thinking-- oh, they knew that we had jewels and that we run away from the Germans, but what we didn't know that they have a plan, a new war, that they want to start a war with Germany, and we were an unwanted element.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't want people on the border that were-- that were Polish citizens.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was told by some other people that they were made to take Russian passports, or approached to take Russian passports.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't remember, not to my best knowledge.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I never remember being-- my parents being approached and taking Russian.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was nobody there that asked them if they want Russian passports or not.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I just remember the KGB coming and putting us in those cattle trains.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--been In Siberia a year and a half.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
